citeinfo.title: Wastewater Land Application Lagoons for Idaho

descript.abstract: These data represent lagoons associated with the Idaho Department of Environmental Quality's Wastewater Land Application program.
descript.purpose: Geographically represent the locations of wastewater land application lagoons for the State of Idaho's environmental programs. Additionally for ground and surface water quality reporting.

attracc.attraccr: Accuracy and reliabiltiy is unknown, or unverified at this time. After IDEQ finishes migrating the legacy database into a central DMBS, we will relate this feature class to it and assess the attribute accuracy at that time.

dataqual.logic: Data was digitized using ArcGIS and ArcView 3.2 polygon editing tools. There are no line intersections. All the data are isolated enclosed polygons. There are no line duplications.
dataqual.complete: IDEQ will continue to revise these data as we get more information on historic lagoons, new permits, and better base data.

horizpa.horizpar: An accuracy test is designed, but has not been completed yet.

procstep.procdesc: Data was digitized as a polygon shapefile on-screen in ArcView 3.2 using existing hard-copy maps (from permits) and either DOQQ (when available) or SPOT 10m satellite imagery (when DOQQs were not available).
The shapefile was converted into a personal geodatabase where it was checked against the WLAP (Hydrologic Management Unit) feature class.
After the personal geodatabase feature class was checked for quality control and metadata written, it was moved into the IDEQ Spatial Database Engine.
